OREON Blast Furnace Auxiliary Manual

Blast furnace auxiliary faults include tuyere cooling leakage, blower vibration, hydraulic valve
failure, cooling water pressure loss, and hot-metal handling conveyor stoppage.

Critical indicators include tuyere water leak, shell temperature spike, irregular blast distribution,
cooling pressure drop, and hydrogen generation risk. Response must follow hot-work permits, controlled
blast reduction, isolation, replacement procedure, and post-repair leak testing.
